<br>
Been to Stonebrunt a number of times, but I can't ever spawn ghostback it seems.  I got the giant panda countless times.<br>
<br>
One of the times I got the giant panda was right after I killed a mountain spiritling, though it was spawned far off so I can't tell if that triggered it.<br>
<br>
If anyone knows of the exact loc where the PH for Ghostback (the giant ape) spawns I would be very appreciative. =)<br>
<br>
Too many hours in this zone already. =( <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzacatac.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 444<br> <font color=#333333>(2/1/02 6:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Smartie Pants!</span><hr size=1> I suspect that the named ones have placeholders.  When the zone came out, and everyone rushed there to see it, I saw both ghostback and the panda that day.  Why?  Probably because there were 80 people in zone killing everything that moves.<br>
<br>
Last time I went out there (I go there to farm cat pelts), I'm the only person in the zone except for 2 lower level people back by the zoneline.  I wandered around the entire zone for nearly 2 hours, never saw a named spawn.  Now I don't have track of course, but I crossed the zone a several times.  There is supposed to be 5 different &quot;named&quot; spawns, I think I would have seen one.<br>
<br>
So good luck, bring a tracker, and just start clearing spawns.  I fought Ghostback just off the pathway leading out of the kitty fort.<br>
